{"at":805831683.716257,"outcome":{"note":{}},"ticketId":"32","detail":"---\n\n## Planning Phase Report — Issue #32\n\n### Stack\n- **Language:** Go 1.25.5\n- **Module:** `github.com\/iksnae\/code-certification`\n- **Test command:** `go test .\/... -count=1`\n- **No external test runner or build tool** (no Makefile used; `justfile` exists but `go test` is the verification command)\n\n---\n\n### 🔴 CRITICAL BLOCKER — Missing `Unsupported` field\n\nThe `Unsupported` field **does not exist** on `domain.CertificationRecord` or any other domain type:\n\n| Type | File | Has Unsupported? |\n|------|------|:--:|\n| `CertificationRecord` | `internal\/domain\/record.go:64-92` | **No** — fields are: `UnitID`, `UnitType`, `UnitPath`, `PolicyVersion`, `Status`, `Grade`, `Score`, `Confidence`, `Dimensions`, `Evidence`, `Observations`, `Actions`, `CertifiedAt`, `ExpiresAt`, `Source`, `RunID`, `Version` |\n| `Status` | `internal\/domain\/record.go:11-20` | **No** — variants are: `StatusCertified`, `StatusCertifiedWithObservations`, `StatusProbationary`, `StatusExpired`, `StatusDecertified`, `StatusExempt` |\n| `Grade` | `internal\/domain\/dimension.go:97-107` | **No** — variants are: `GradeA`, `GradeAMinus`, `GradeBPlus`, `GradeB`, `GradeC`, `GradeD`, `GradeF` |\n\nThe parent issue #25 (per engagement history) was supposed to add this: *\"Grade and CertificationRecord need N\/A and Unsupported additions.\"* That work has not landed. The non-goal says *\"Do not modify domain types\"* — which means this issue cannot add the field itself. **You must decide: add the field anyway, wait for #25, or detect unsupported records by another mechanism.**\n\n---\n\n### The 4 target functions — exactly what to change\n\n**1. `internal\/report\/detailed.go:69-84` — `computeDimensionAverages`**\n```go\nfor _, r := range records {\n    for dim, score := range r.Dimensions {\n        sums[dim.String()] += score\n        counts[dim.String()]++\n    }\n}\n```\n→ Needs a `if r.Unsupported { continue }` guard at the top of the loop body (or equivalent) so unsupported records don't pollute dimension averages.\n\n**2. `internal\/report\/full.go:118-157` — `buildLanguageDetail`**\n```go\nfor _, r := range records {\n    lang := r.UnitID.Language()\n    a, ok := accum[lang]\n    ...\n    a.scores = append(a.scores, r.Score)\n    a.grades[r.Grade.String()]++\n    if r.Status.IsPassing() { a.passing++ }\n}\n```\n→ Needs a `if r.Unsupported { continue }` guard to skip unsupported records in per-language score\/grades\/passing counts. Note: `buildLanguageDetail` is called from both `GenerateFullReport` (full.go:81) and `GenerateCard` (card.go:80).\n\n**3. `internal\/report\/health.go:37-74` — `Health()`**\n```go\nfor _, r := range records {\n    totalScore += r.Score\n    switch r.Status { ... }\n}\nh.PassRate = float64(passing) \/ float64(h.TotalUnits)\nh.AverageScore = totalScore \/ float64(h.TotalUnits)\n```\n→ Needs an `if r.Unsupported { continue }` guard. Also needs to decrement `h.TotalUnits` (currently `len(records)`) or use a separate counter for \"counted\" units. Both `h.PassRate` and `h.AverageScore` denominators use `h.TotalUnits` and would be skewed by unsupported records.\n\n**4. `internal\/report\/card.go:57-82` — `GenerateCard()`**\n```go\nc.TotalUnits = len(records)\n...\nfor _, r := range records {\n    totalScore += r.Score\n    c.GradeDistribution[r.Grade.String()]++\n    ...\n}\nc.OverallScore = totalScore \/ float64(c.TotalUnits)\nc.PassRate = float64(c.Passing) \/ float64(c.TotalUnits)\n```\n→ Needs an `if r.Unsupported { continue }` guard. `TotalUnits` must be a counted value, not `len(records)`. Both `OverallScore` and `PassRate` denominators use `TotalUnits`.\n\n---\n\n### Shared dependency chain\n\n`GenerateFullReport` (full.go:71) calls both `GenerateCard` (which calls `buildLanguageDetail`) and `computeDimensionAverages`. `Detailed` (detailed.go:48-52) calls `Health()` and `computeDimensionAverages` and `computeLanguageBreakdowns` (a separate, local-only function that also needs the Unsupported skip). The skip needs to be consistent across all call sites.\n\n---\n\n### Existing N\/A handling (not to be changed)\n\nThe `gradeEmoji` function (card.go:275-287) already returns `\"⚪\"` for unknown grades — this covers the \"N\/A\" rendering for unsupported languages. The empty-records `\"N\/A\"` return in `GenerateCard` (card.go:63) is also already in place. These are **not** to be changed per the non-goal.\n\n---\n\n### Tests\n\nAll four test files use `make*Record` helpers that construct `domain.CertificationRecord` structs without any `Unsupported` field. Tests will continue to pass as-is if the field is added (it defaults to `false` for existing records), but **new tests should be written** to verify that records with `Unsupported: true` are skipped in each of the four functions. The existing `TestGenerateCard_Empty` (card_test.go:73-76) which checks `\"N\/A\"` on nil input must still pass.\n\n---\n\n### Verification\n\n```bash\ngo test .\/... -count=1\n```","id":"32-228","phase":"planning"}
