{"ticketId":"32","phase":"decompose","at":805852566.533349,"outcome":{"note":{}},"detail":"---\n\n## DECOMPOSE REPORT — Issue #32: Skip Unsupported records in aggregate calculations\n\n### 1. PROJECT CONTEXT\n\n- **Module:** `github.com\/iksnae\/code-certification` (Go 1.25.5)\n- **Test command:** `go test .\/... -count=1`\n- **Domain package:** `internal\/domain\/` — zero-external-dependency core types (`CertificationRecord`, `DimensionScores`, `Grade`, `Status`, `UnitID`, etc.)\n- **Report package:** `internal\/report\/` — report generators consuming `[]domain.CertificationRecord`\n- **Engine package:** `internal\/engine\/` — `CertifyUnit()` in `pipeline.go` builds `CertificationRecord`; `scorer.go` computes dimension scores. Both are **non-goals** for this issue.\n\n### 2. CURRENT STATE OF `CertificationRecord`\n\n**File:** `internal\/domain\/record.go` (lines 70–94)\n\nThe struct currently has **NO `Unsupported` field**. The approved plan comment on the issue says to add:\n```go\nUnsupported bool `json:\"unsupported,omitempty\"`\n```\nThis must happen **first** — all four report consumers need to check `r.Unsupported`. Default `false` is backward-compatible: all existing tests and call sites (e.g. `CertifyUnit` in `pipeline.go`) don't set it, so it stays `false` and nothing breaks. The record store (`internal\/record\/store.go`) serializes via a separate `recordJSON` struct that also lacks the field; this is fine for now.\n\n### 3. FOUR TARGET FILES — EXACT CHANGE POINTS\n\n#### A. `internal\/report\/health.go` — `Health()` (lines 35–69)\n\n**Current behavior:** Uses `len(records)` as `TotalUnits` and as denominator for both `PassRate` and `AverageScore`. Every record increments status counters and adds to `totalScore`.\n\n**Required change:**\n- Add `if r.Unsupported { continue }` at top of loop (line ~52)\n- Track a `counted` (or `effective`) int for the non-unsupported count\n- Use `counted` for `TotalUnits`, PassRate denominator, and AverageScore denominator\n- Edge case: when all records are unsupported (`counted == 0`), return empty `HealthReport{}` (already handled — the `len(records) == 0` guard at L36 will NOT trigger because `len(records) > 0`, but after skipping all, `counted` would be 0 causing a division-by-zero. Need to add a guard: if `counted == 0`, return `HealthReport{}`)\n\n#### B. `internal\/report\/card.go` — `GenerateCard()` (lines 67–100)\n\n**Current behavior:** Uses `len(records)` as `TotalUnits`, denominator for `OverallScore` and `PassRate`. The empty-records guard at L74 returns `N\/A`.\n\n**Required change:**\n- Add `if r.Unsupported { continue }` at top of loop (line ~79)\n- Track a `counted` int; use it for `TotalUnits` and denominators\n- After loop: if `counted == 0`, return N\/A card (the existing empty guard triggers first since `len(records) > 0` is still true, so need to add a post-loop `counted == 0` check)\n- `buildTopIssues()` also iterates records — the issue says \"skip Unsupported records from the total count used in GenerateCard()\" but doesn't explicitly call out `buildTopIssues`. However, since unsupported records shouldn't appear in top issues either (they'd have fabricated scores), the same guard should apply there.\n\n#### C. `internal\/report\/detailed.go` — `computeDimensionAverages()` (lines 83–94)\n\n**Current behavior:** Sums dimension scores and counts across all records.\n\n**Required change:**\n- Add `if r.Unsupported { continue }` at top of loop (line ~86)\n\n#### D. `internal\/report\/detailed.go` — `computeLanguageBreakdowns()` (lines 96–119)\n\n**Current behavior:** Counts language totals, sums scores, counts passing across all records.\n\n**Required change:**\n- Add `if r.Unsupported { continue }` at top of loop (line ~99)\n\n#### E. `internal\/report\/full.go` — `buildLanguageDetail()` (lines 144–179)\n\n**Current behavior:** Uses a `langAccum` struct with `[]float64` slices; iterates all records building per-language score slices, grade distributions, and passing counts.\n\n**Required change:**\n- Add `if r.Unsupported { continue }` at top of loop (line ~150)\n\n### 4. FUNCTIONS NOT MENTIONED BUT NOTED\n\nThese functions in `detailed.go` iterate records but are **not** in the issue scope:\n- `findExpiringSoon()` (L121) — not called out; Unsupported records likely won't be expiring\n- `findHighestRisk()` (L133) — not called out\n- `findFailing()` (L145) — not called out\n- `findRecurrentlyFailing()` (L153) — not called out\n\nThese are intentionally left unchanged per the issue.\n\n### 5. EXISTING TEST LANDSCAPE\n\nAll four test files use helper functions that construct `CertificationRecord` without setting any `Unsupported` field. After adding the field with default `false`, all existing tests continue to pass unchanged.\n\n**Key existing test for empty\/N\/A behavior:** `TestGenerateCard_Empty` in `card_test.go` — passes `nil` and expects `OverallGrade == \"N\/A\"`. This must continue to pass.\n\n**Test files to extend with Unsupported subtests:**\n- `internal\/report\/health_test.go` — add subtests with `Unsupported: true` records\n- `internal\/report\/card_test.go` — add subtests with `Unsupported: true` records\n- `internal\/report\/detailed_test.go` — add subtests with `Unsupported: true` records\n- `internal\/report\/full_test.go` — add subtests with `Unsupported: true` records\n\n### 6. EDGE CASES & DIVISION-BY-ZERO\n\n- **All records unsupported** → `Health()` must return empty struct (guard needed: `if counted == 0 { return HealthReport{} }`). `GenerateCard()` must return N\/A card. `Detailed()` must return empty detailed (already delegates to `Health()`).\n- **Mixed supported\/unsupported** → unsupported records contribute **zero** to sums, counts, grade distributions, and passing\/failing tallies.\n- **`buildLanguageDetail`** uses `len(a.scores)` as denominator for average — if all records for a language are unsupported, that language won't appear in the map at all (because the `langAccum` is never created). This is correct.\n- **`computeDimensionAverages`** uses `counts[dim] > 0` guard — safe if no supported records have that dimension.\n- **`computeLanguageBreakdowns`** uses `scores[lang] \/ float64(total)` — safe only if `total > 0`; if all records for a language are unsupported, it won't be in the map.\n\n### 7. SUMMARY OF WORK ITEMS (for the implement phase)\n\n1. **Add `Unsupported bool` to `domain.CertificationRecord`** in `internal\/domain\/record.go`\n2. **Guard 5 loops** with `if r.Unsupported { continue }`:\n   - `Health()` in `health.go`\n   - `GenerateCard()` in `card.go` (also `buildTopIssues`)\n   - `computeDimensionAverages()` in `detailed.go`\n   - `computeLanguageBreakdowns()` in `detailed.go`\n   - `buildLanguageDetail()` in `full.go`\n3. **Fix denominators** in `Health()` and `GenerateCard()` to use a counted-total instead of `len(records)`\n4. **Add division-by-zero guards** for the all-unsupported edge case\n5. **Add subtests** to all four `_test.go` files with `Unsupported: true` records\n6. **Verify:** `go test .\/... -count=1`","id":"32-1141"}
